# Copy to .env. See IMPLEMENTATION.md §2 and ADR 0014.
#
# On the server this file IS the secret store: Compose loads it into `web` and
# `worker` with `env_file:`, so everything marked SECRET below lives here. It is
# git-ignored and docker-ignored, and that is the only thing keeping these
# values out of the repo and out of a public image. Never bake one into an image.
#
# The database password and URL are the exception. They stay file-based Compose
# `secrets:` in ./secrets/ (see secrets/README.md), because they were deployed
# that way. The config package reads `X_FILE` for any `X`, and a mounted `X_FILE`
# WINS over an `X` set here: that is what stops the localhost DATABASE_URL below,
# which the host-side `deno task` flows need, from following the same .env into a
# container and pointing it at a database that is not there.
#
# Two ways to write a value wrong, both silent:
#
#   Quote anything containing `$`. Compose expands it in an unquoted or
#   double-quoted value, so SESSION_SECRET=abc$def reaches the container as
#   `abc`. Single quotes survive: SESSION_SECRET='abc$def'.
#
#   Never leave a key blank (`FOO=`). Comment it out instead. A blank is read as
#   "not configured" (packages/config/load.ts), so it is not an error, it just
#   is not what you meant.
#
# Config fails loud at boot: a service that needs a value and cannot find it
# exits, naming everything that was wrong, rather than starting half-configured.
# Each group below is only required by the phase that reads it, so Phase 1
# genuinely needs nothing but the Core block.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------- Core (Phase 1)
# Local only. In Compose this comes from ./secrets/database_url via
# DATABASE_URL_FILE, which beats whatever is set here.
DATABASE_URL=postgres://7r:7r@localhost:5432/7r
PUBLIC_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8085
LOG_LEVEL=info

# ------------------------------------------------------------- Worker (Phase 1)
WORKER_INTERNAL_PORT=8080

# ------------------------------------------------------- Discord (Phases 2 & 4)
# The four app values below all come from ONE Discord application: 7R_Bot, ours,
# already in the guild, previously the /loa bot. The 2019 bot's account and token
# are not reused (ARCHITECTURE §7, ADR 0015).
#
# A third silent way to get this wrong, on top of the two at the top of the file:
# take the token from one application and the public key from another. Every
# interaction then 401s, and Discord responds by removing the endpoint URL, which
# presents as the bot going quiet rather than as an error.
# DISCORD_GUILD_ID=305471712546390017             # the guild does not change
# DISCORD_CLIENT_ID=                              # 7R_Bot's application id: OAuth login AND command registration
# DISCORD_CLIENT_SECRET=                          # SECRET; same application
# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=                              # SECRET; 7R_Bot's (Bot -> Reset Token), NOT the 2019 bot's
# DISCORD_PUBLIC_KEY=                             # interactions Ed25519 verify; same application as the token
# DISCORD_ADMIN_ROLE_IDS=                         # comma-separated; admin is a single boolean derived from these
# SESSION_SECRET=                                 # SECRET; Better Auth cookie signing
# ARMA_SERVER_PASSWORD=                           # SECRET; what /server hands to members. Every member knows it, which
#                                                 # does not make it publishable: this repo is public. The current value
#                                                 # already is, and stays so, knowingly (ARCHITECTURE §7). Keeping it here
#                                                 # rather than in source is what makes changing it cheap if that ever bites.

# ---------------------------------------------------------- Steam (Phase 2)
# Steam OpenID is stateless: no API key is needed to log in.
# STEAM_REALM=https://7th-ranger.com

# ----------------------------------------------- Web -> worker API (Phase 2)
# The Compose network only: never proxied, never public.
# WORKER_INTERNAL_URL=http://worker:8080
# WORKER_INTERNAL_TOKEN=                          # SECRET; shared between web and worker

# ------------------------------------------------- TeamSpeak (Phases 3 & 5)
# TS_QUERY_HOST=ts.7th-ranger.com
# TS_QUERY_PORT=10022                             # SSH. NEVER 10011: raw ServerQuery is cleartext and this host is public
# TS_QUERY_USER=                                  # SECRET
# TS_QUERY_PASS=                                  # SECRET
# TS_VIRTUALSERVER_ID=1
# TS_OPERATIONS_CHANNEL_CID=                      # the single Operations channel
# TS_BOT_NICKNAME=7R Bot

# --------------------------------------------------- Role sync (Phase 3)
# ROLE_SYNC_INTERVAL_SECONDS=300
# SYNC_DRY_RUN=true                               # start true; flip only after a preview looks right
# SYNC_MAX_REMOVALS=5                             # blast-radius guard: a pass touching more members than this HALTS

# ------------------------------------------- Ops & attendance (Phases 4 & 5)
# Saturday only. Mission time 20:00-23:00; the Discord event runs to 23:30.
# OP_TIMEZONE=Europe/Amsterdam
# OP_WEEKLY_CRON=0 20 * * 6
# OP_ATTENDANCE_START=20:00
# OP_ATTENDANCE_END=23:00
# OP_EVENT_END=23:30
# ATTENDANCE_MIN_MINUTES=60
# ATTENDANCE_SAMPLE_SECONDS=90

# ----------------------------------------------------------------- Alerts
# SECRET; the worker posts its own errors here. Make it in Discord: Server
# Settings -> Integrations -> Webhooks -> New Webhook, pointed at a private
# staff channel. Anyone holding the URL can post to that channel.
# Nothing reads this yet: alertSchema has no loader (packages/config/mod.ts).
# ERROR_ALERT_DISCORD_WEBHOOK=https://discord.com/api/webhooks/<id>/<token>
